'''Roberto Tozzi''' (born [[17 December]],[[1958]]) was an [[Italy|Italian]] athlete who competed mainly in the 400 metres.

He competed for an Italy in the [[Athletics at the 1980 Summer Olympics|1980 Summer Olympics]] held in [[Moscow]], [[Soviet Union]] in the 4 x 400 metre relay where he won the bronze medal with his team mates [[Stefano Malinverni]], [[Mauro Zuliani]] and [[Pietro Mennea]].

